#lang ivy1.7

# =============================================================================
# Pattern:     before_after_template
# Source:      BGP ivy_bgp_speaker_behavior.ivy
# Description: Before/after monitor pattern for constraining generated messages.
#              Uses `if _generating` guards to apply constraints only when Ivy
#              is the sender (test generator), not when processing received msgs.
#              Defines per-message-type before monitors and helper actions.
#
# Placeholders:
#   {prot}             - protocol name, lowercase (e.g., "bgp", "quic")
#   {PROT}             - protocol name, UPPERCASE
#   {id_type}          - identifier type for endpoints (e.g., "bgp_id", "cid")
#   {variant_name}     - top-level message name (e.g., "header_message")
#   {msg_type_enum}    - enum for message types (e.g., "bgp_message_type")
#   {ivy_instance}     - Ivy-side instance name (e.g., "bgp_ivy_instance")
#   {impl_instance}    - impl-side instance name (e.g., "bgp_impl_instance")
#
# Cross-references:
#   - Constrains:  variant_frame_template.ivy events
#   - Included by: test files (e.g., {prot}_test_*.ivy)
#   - Depends on:  shim file for helper actions and state variables
#
# Decision points:
#   1. Which fields to constrain via `require` in each before monitor
#   2. Which fields to assign via `:=` (fixing values vs constraining)
#   3. Whether to track cumulative state (e.g., header_length, header_payload)
# =============================================================================

# --- Include dependencies ---
# TODO: adjust includes for your protocol
# include order
# include {prot}_infer
# include file
# include random_value

